<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE60018FF38F393450CF839" bold="true" box="[151,314,1954,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">FIGURES 1–4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE60018FE90F39545EBF839" box="[319,477,1955,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tedeschii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE60018FE90F39545EBF839" box="[319,477,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Meira tedeschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A212063BFFE60018FE4CF395462DF838" box="[483,539,1956,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 1. penis in lateral view; 2. apex of the penis in dorsal view; 3. spermatheca; 4. coxites of the ovipositor.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEA6752FFE5001BFF68F5BB45E5FE45" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFF68F5BB4635FE20" bold="true" box="[199,515,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Derivation of species name.</emphasis>
This species is named in honour of my dear friend and colleague Michele Tedeschi, who was the first to collect it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F34D9FFE5001BFF68F5E1401BF86C" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEA6752FFE5001BFF68F5E145CAFE66" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,764]" box="[199,508,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFF68F5E1456FFE66" bold="true" box="[199,345,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Distribution.</emphasis>
Island of Elba.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA6752FFE5001BFF68F5C345BFFDAD" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFF68F5C345BEFD88" bold="true" box="[199,392,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Ecological notes.</emphasis>
The specimens of the 
<typeStatus id="54EED9F0FFE5001BFD26F5C34681FD88" box="[649,695,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">type</typeStatus>
series were collected at 
<number id="3D9D7575FFE5001BFC62F5C347C3FD88" box="[973,1013,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" value="150.0">150</number>
meters above sea level, mainly under 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFF38F625455DFDAD" box="[151,363,532,556]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Lavandula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stoechas">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFF38F625455DFDAD" box="[151,363,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Lavandula stoechas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA6752FFE5001BFF68F60946C0FD7D" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFF68F60945BAFDCE" bold="true" box="[199,396,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
The new species (fig. 
<number id="3D9D7575FFE5001BFDD4F60946BFFDCE" box="[635,649,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" value="5.0">5</number>
) is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFC3DF60947C3FDCE" box="[914,1013,567,591]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diottii">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFC3DF60947C3FDCE" box="[914,1013,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. diottii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of additional spicules in the internal sac of the penis, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFDA0F66B464EFDF0" box="[527,632,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baudii">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFDA0F66B464EFDF0" box="[527,632,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. baudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFD27F66B46CDFDF0" box="[648,763,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFD27F66B46CDFDF0" box="[648,763,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFCA4F66B4024FDF0" authority="Pierotti, 2012" authorityName="Pierotti" authorityYear="2012" box="[779,1042,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabina">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFCA4F66B4741FDF0" box="[779,887,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. sabina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC41AA3FFE5001BFCD0F66B4024FDF0" author="Pierotti" box="[895,1042,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" refString="Pierotti, H. (2012) Peritelini nuovi o interessanti della fauna w-paleartica. XVII. Due nuove specie italiane del genere Meira Jacquelin du Val (Coleoptera, Curculionidae, Entiminae). Doriana, suppl. agli Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; di Genova, 376, 1 - 7. [VIII]" type="journal article" year="2012">
Pierotti, 
<number id="3D9D7575FFE5001BFC72F66B4024FDF0" box="[989,1042,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFBE5F66B4179FDF0" authority="Pierotti, 2013" authorityName="Pierotti" authorityYear="2013" box="[1098,1359,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbra">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFBE5F66B4082FDF0" box="[1098,1204,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. umbra</emphasis>
Pierotti, 
<number id="3D9D7575FFE5001BFAB5F66B4179FDF0" box="[1306,1359,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</taxonomicName>
by the more slender shape, the elytra with parallel or very weakly rounded sides and with almost flat interstriae, the elytral setae recumbent or subrecumbent also on the shoulders, and especially by the coxites of the ovipositor narrower and sclerotised in the preapical region. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFD3DF6F3472EFD58" box="[658,792,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tedeschii">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFD3DF6F3472EFD58" box="[658,792,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. tedeschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFC02F6F3402CFD58" box="[941,1050,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabina">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFC02F6F3402CFD58" box="[941,1050,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. sabina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFBFBF6F340FEFD58" box="[1108,1224,706,729]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFBFBF6F340FEFD58" box="[1108,1224,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the funicle less thick, and from the latter also by the elytral setae shorter.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2A37DAFFE5001BFF38F37E467CF8E7" box="[151,586,1871,1894]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
<paragraph id="8BEA6752FFE5001BFF38F37E467CF8E7" blockId="2.[151,586,1871,1894]" box="[151,586,1871,1894]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFF38F37E4524F8E4" bold="true" box="[151,274,1871,1893]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFEB6F3614581F8E4" box="[281,439,1872,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tedeschii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFEB6F3614581F8E4" box="[281,439,1872,1893]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Meira tedeschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A212063BFFE5001BFE12F36145C0F8E4" box="[445,502,1872,1893]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: habitus
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEA6752FFE5001BFF68F3A0401BF86C" blockId="2.[151,1437,1937,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
The already highlighted intraspecific variability of many characters, and in particular that of the apical part of the penis (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC41AA3FFE5001BFF4FF382454EF84B" author="Pierotti" box="[224,376,1971,1994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" refString="Pierotti, H. (2011) Peritelini nouveaux ou interessants de la faune ouest-mediterraneenne. XV. Trois nouvelles especes francaises du genre Meira Jacquelin du Val (Coleoptera, Curculionidae, Entiminae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 116 (4), 505 - 508." type="journal article" year="2011">
Pierotti, 
<number id="3D9D7575FFE5001BFEEFF382454EF84B" box="[320,376,1971,1994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), leads one to hypothesize that the Italian species—with the exception perhaps of 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFAABF3824159F84B" box="[1284,1391,1970,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baudii">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFAABF3824159F84B" box="[1284,1391,1970,1994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. baudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C551CD1FFE5001BFAD0F38244E1F86C" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diottii">
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFAD0F38244E1F86C" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. diottii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="B921BB40FFE5001BFEBEF3E74590F86C" box="[273,422,2006,2029]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">M. oenotria—</emphasis>
are entities still under differentiation from a unique ancestor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
